topics.body:
So on politics side chances are pretty high that Hillary is going to be our next president.

Eh; she may not be ideal but I'll vote for her because she'll be metaphorically dead on arrival.

Why would I intentionally vote for something like this and what do I mean by this?  Easy; right now both houses of congress are controlled by republicans.  The general rule of thumb for presidents is that unless something drastic happens after 2 years they essentially become more concerned with keeping their party electable.  By the time Democrats gain a super majority of both houses it will already be time for the next presidential election.

Tl:dr; in 2016 I'm not voting for a liberal; rather I'm voting for a congress that by the time they gain enough seats for pushing ideology it'll already be time for the next election.
